[h4 id=Nvr 
	" NVR
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This chipset does not pull the default NVR from a file - just make sure that in 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/nvr/
	]code
	" there is no NVR named after your config file (e.g. if your config is named 
	[code 
		"windowsxp
	]code
	", delete any file called 
	[code 
		"windowsxp.ga686bx.nvr
	]code
	".)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you've launched the machine before, you'll need to delete the 
	[code 
		".nvr
	]code
	" file as well as 
	[code 
		"~/.pcem/roms/ga686bx/flash.bin
	]code
	".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=WindowsXpLibtasMovieFile 
	" Windows XP libTAS movie file
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"At this point, you can run the Windows XP installation movie if you want our exact hashes:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		(__wikiLink|href=/UserFiles/Info/638629741787395345|implicitdisplaytext=UserFiles/Info/638629741787395345)
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Note that libTAS 1.4.4 and older has a memory leak caused by OSD in long movies, so you'll need to disable it in 
	[em 
		"Video -> OSD
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
