[h3 id=Installation 
	" Installation
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"The following section outlines every step needed to recreate the outcome generated by the Windows XP installation verification movie file if you need to perform the installation manually.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=SettingUpBios 
	" Setting up BIOS
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Now you can boot up your configuration. On the bootup screen, press the 
	[code 
		"Delete
	]code
	" key to go to the BIOS menu. Select 
	[em 
		"BIOS Features Setup
	]em
	" and press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" then go down to 
	[em 
		"Boot Sequence
	]em
	" and use 
	[code 
		"PageUp
	]code
	"/
	[code 
		"PageDown
	]code
	" to select 
	[em 
		"C,CDROM,A
	]em
	":
	$LF
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/BIOSSetup.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This will allow you to boot from the XP CD at first because the hard drive is blank, and then when the hard drive becomes bootable it will use that instead. Press 
	[code 
		"Escape
	]code
	" and then select 
	[em 
		"Save & Exit Setup
	]em
	" on the main menu. Press 
	[code 
		"Y
	]code
	" and then 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" at the prompt.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=FormattingHardDrive 
	" Formatting hard drive
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"When the PC reboots, just wait and it will automatically boot from the XP CD. Once it's done loading you will see this screen:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/XPSetupStart.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" to continue, and press 
	[code 
		"F8
	]code
	" to agree to the license agreement.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The setup will now partition and format the hard drive for you. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/CreatePartition.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" to partition the unpartitioned space.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/FormatPartition.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Select 
	[em 
		"Format the partition using the FAT file system
	]em
	", press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	", and then press 
	[code 
		"Enter
	]code
	" again to format the partition.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=XpInstallation 
	" XP installation
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Once the formatting is done, it will start copying files over. This will take a while.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/CopyingFiles.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"When it's done copying files, the PC will reboot and put you into the proper installer. It will install some more things, and then put you on this screen.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/RegionalScreen.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"We will be installing language packs so languages like Japanese will appear correctly. Click 
	[em 
		"Customize...
	]em
	" and go to the 
	[em 
		"Languages
	]em
	" tab.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/LanguagePacks.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Check both options in this window. When it pops up a message about hard drive space, just click 
	[em 
		"OK
	]em
	". Once both of these options are checked, click 
	[em 
		"OK
	]em
	". Wait for it to install the packs. Once it's done, you can click 
	[em 
		"Next
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/XPName.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Put 
	[code 
		"TAS
	]code
	" and 
	[code 
		"TASVideos
	]code
	" for 
	[em 
		"Name
	]em
	" and 
	[em 
		"Organization
	]em
	" respectively, and click 
	[em 
		"Next
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/KeyScreen.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"On the product key screen, do not put in a key! Click 
	[em 
		"Next
	]em
	" and it will pop up a window asking you if you want to enter your product key now. 
	[b 
		"Click 
		[em 
			"No
		]em
		" on this.
	]b
	" This will allow you to have a 30 day trial before you need to enter one. On the 
	[em 
		"Computer Name
	]em
	" screen, just click 
	[em 
		"Next
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/TimeZoneScreen.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"On the time screen, select 
	[em 
		"(GMT) Greenwich Mean Time
	]em
	" for the time zone and uncheck the daylight savings box. Don't worry about the time and date, libTAS will inject its own time. Click 
	[em 
		"Next
	]em
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/InstallingWindows.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The installer will now take a while to finish up the installation. Enjoy the Windows XP fun facts!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/AdjustResolution.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Once it's done installing, it will reboot again. Press 
	[em 
		"OK
	]em
	" to adjust the screen resolution and it will go up to 800 x 600. Press 
	[em 
		"OK
	]em
	" again after it's changed.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/PleaseWait.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"At this point, PCem is known to cause Windows XP to freeze sometimes, causing the following 
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Out-of-box_experience rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"OOBE
	]a
	" sequence to never show up. If that happens, just reboot the machine and you'll get into the 
	[a class=intlink href=#SoundBlasterInstallation 
		"usual Windows XP desktop environment
	]a
	" which works normally.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://files.tasvideos.org/common/Wiki/pcem/windows/configurations/FirstSetup.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
